President Joseph R. Biden, Jr. has declared a major disaster in the Commonwealth of Kentucky due to severe winter storms, landslides, and mudslides that occurred from February 8 to February 19, 2021. This declaration allows for federal assistance to supplement recovery efforts in the affected areas. Federal funding will be available for emergency work and the repair or replacement of damaged facilities in numerous counties. Hazard mitigation measures for the entire commonwealth will also be eligible for federal funding. John Brogan has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations, with the possibility of additional designations in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk.